## Rules for Prompts

- **Highly specific**: exact hex colors, explicit layout (sidebar width, header height), explicit typography
- **UI-first**: every prompt = a realistic app screenshot, NOT an illustration or abstract graphic
- **Zero overlap**: each direction must feel like a different design studio made it
- **Direction 4 = experimental**: challenge UI conventions creatively, remain usable
- **Realistic content**: actual product content, no lorem ipsum, no placeholder text
- **Format**: `"prompt: "..."` must be on a single line, in double quotes

## Design Direction Dimensions to Vary

| Dimension | Examples |
|-----------|---------|
| Color philosophy | Monochromatic dark / Full-spectrum neon / Earth tones / Pastel + dark |
| Layout structure | Sidebar + main / Full-width editorial / Radial / Split-panel |
| Typography | Geometric sans / Serif editorial / Condensed display / Mono |
| Material feel | Glass morphism / Brushed metal / Matte flat / Paper texture |
| Spatial density | Information-dense / Breathing whitespace / Compressed/modular |

## After Creating design-exploration.md

**DO NOT attempt to generate images yourself.**
**DO NOT report a missing image-generation API key as a blocker.**

The pipeline orchestrator handles image generation automatically after you finish:
1. It calls NanoBanana Pro with your prompts
2. Presents all variants to the user for selection
3. Passes the approved variant to the Design Translator agent

Your Handoff section should only mention blockers related to the app's own requirements (missing backend keys, unclear specs, etc.) — never image generation.

End with a brief Handoff note.
